cajho@uno.edu writes:
: I am curious as to how non-digital voice encryption is done.  Can someone 
: point me in the right direction?
: 
: Thanks,
: 
: Craig Johnston
: cajho@uno.edu
: 

References:

KAHN67	David Kahn. The Codebreakers. Macmillan: 1967.
	There is a chapter entitled "Censors, Scramblers, and Spies."
	which describes the basics of speech scrambling.
KAHN84	David Kahn. "Cryptology and the origins of spread spectrum." in
	IEEE Spectrum, September 1984
	This is an excellent article which also contains references to
	SIGSALY - the WWII voice scrambler, and to its Soviet counterpart.
GOLD91	B Goldburg, E Dawson, S Sridharan. "The Automated Cryptanalysis of
	Analog Speech Scramblers." in EUROCRYPT '91 - Advances in Cryptology,
	Springer Verlag: 1991.
	Describes cryptanalysis of the following scramblers: Hopping Window,
	Bandsplitter, and permuted DFT.

These sources also have references which you should try to check out.
Good luck in your search.

Joe	pjhong@clio.rad.sunysb.edu
